# TDD Guidelines

## Core Principles

1. **Red-Green-Refactor**: Write a failing test first, implement just enough to pass, then clean up.
2. **One assertion per test**: Each test should verify one specific behavior.
3. **Test names describe behavior**: `test_returns_404_when_user_not_found`, not `test_user`.

## Workflow

1. Write a test that describes the expected behavior
2. Run the test — it must FAIL (red)
3. Write the minimum code to make the test pass (green)
4. Run all tests — they must ALL pass
5. Refactor code without changing behavior
6. Run all tests again — they must STILL pass

## Definition of Done

- [ ] Test written BEFORE implementation
- [ ] Test covers happy path
- [ ] Test covers at least one edge case
- [ ] Test covers error handling
- [ ] All tests pass (no regressions)
- [ ] Code is clean and follows project conventions
- [ ] No linting errors

## What NOT to Do

- Don't write implementation code before tests
- Don't skip edge case testing
- Don't mark a task done if any test is failing
- Don't disable tests to make the suite pass
